               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1400" notAfter="1500">1400-1500</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">The old church is said to have been founded by King Zarʾā Yāʿqob (r. <date>1438-1468</date>); the monastic community was established by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">King Yoḥannǝs IV</persName> (r. <date>1872-1889</date>). The religious site might have existed in the Aksumite time.</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Gadām. The monastic community consists of at least 15 monks. 
</ab>
                  <ab type="description">
                     <figure>
                        <graphic url="Sites/QDGM.tif">
                           <desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</desc>
                        </graphic>
                     </figure>13 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm001">QDGM-001</ref> ʺThe Four Gospelsʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm002">QDGM-002</ref> ʺPraise of Godʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm003">QDGM-003</ref> ʺOctateuchʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm004">QDGM-004</ref> ʺPsalterʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm005">QDGM-005</ref> ʺPraise of Godʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm006">QDGM-006</ref> ʺThe Harp of Praiseʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm007">QDGM-007</ref> ʺFour Gospelsʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm008">QDGM-008</ref> ʺThe Book of the Spirtual Elderʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm009">QDGM-009</ref> ʺCommentary to the Pauline Epistlesʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm010">QDGM-010</ref> ʺThe History of the Apostlesʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm011">QDGM-011</ref> ʺPsalterʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm012">QDGM-012</ref> ʺVita of ʾArägawiʺ; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm013">QDGM-013</ref> ʺVita of Kirosʺ. The collection includes more than 120 Mss.</ab>
                
                  <ab type="tabot">
                     <measure quantity="7"/>Tābots of <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">Mary</persName>, <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh#n3MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</persName>, <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">George</persName>, 
                     <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10581Zamika">ʾAragāwi</persName>, <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10775Trinity">Trinity</persName>, <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/CovenantMercy">Kidāna Mǝḥrat</ref>, 
                     probably <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Haymanot</persName>.</ab>
